              <tr> 
                <td height="622" valign="top" colspan="2" bgcolor="#004142">&nbsp;<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">How Not To Let the Game Die</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Rating</Font></TD><TD><IMG SRC="images/a4.gif" BORDER=0><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=3186"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=3186"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=444">Rypcord "Rypcord" Kline</A></FONT></TD></TR><!-- 444 --><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">A good way to not let the Game die, without being totally unoriginal or obvious.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Article</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I&#146;m going to explain how to keep this great game alive, but without being too overly redundant or obvious, or boring {hopefully}.<br>
<br>
First, is daily tournaments. <br>
<br>
Though, over time this easily could kill the game off for you, so how do you have daily tournaments {that are sanctioned!} that do not ruin the game for yourselves?<br>
<br>
Thats simple! First off, every 3 days should be the regular tournament. A regular swiss tournament, with all cards from all sets legal.<br>
<br>
Then, on Monday have it be an Episode 1 only tournament. This way, people can use all of their favorite Jedi without worrying about Mr. Emperor, Mara, and Vader giving them a good old fashion probe with his lightsaber.<br>
<br>
Tuesday can be a Bespin and Beyond tournament. Wow, boy am I going Almost Old School! The BnB tournament, should be from Bespin to either Special Edition, or Endor, your choice. I prefer stopping it at the SpEd range though, so as theres not to much to defend against.<br>
<br>
Wednesday is the regular tournament.<br>
<br>
Thursday, can be a Endor/DSII tournament. Where only cards from Endor, DSII, or cards found in the DSII Starter Decks may be used. These tournaments can be alot of fun!<br>
<br>
Friday can be a Old School tournament. Where it involves cards from Premier-A New Hope-Hoth, and if you want, Dagobah. This is always a fun tournament, just due to the nostalgia. <br>
<br>
Saturday can be any kind of tournament you wish. Whatever you guys feel like on the day, make it.<br>
<br>
And Sunday is the other &quot;normal&quot; day. Where a regular tournament is held.<br>
<br>
So your schedule should go like this:<br>
<br>
Sunday-------Monday-----Tuesday----Wednesday-----Thursday----Friday-----Saturday<br>
<br>
Regular-----Ep1-------BnB--------Regular---------DSII/Endor---Old-School---Whatever--Goes<br>
<br>
Hopefully the above chart works when you read this Article.<br>
<br>
But Rypcord.... what about Prize Support?<br>
<br>
There may be some spoilers involved in the Prize Support section, so please, read at your own risk!<br>
<br>
Appropriate Spoiler Space:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Okay. Here goes the Prize Support:<br>
<br>
<br>
This could be something fun. You could, for instance make up JUST ONE CARD, of your own. Thats very strong, but not broken. A card, which is not an effect or anything that can begin on table, so as not to give the player with it an immediate advantage. So, you can make the prize support this card. And, whoever wins the tournament gets the card to be able to use in the other tournaments until someone else wins a tournament. This promotes a good friendly competition. A few cards I suggest may be:<br>
<br>
Dark Side: <br>
<br>
Count Dooku:<br>
Deploy: 6<br>
Forfeit: 9<br>
Power: 6<br>
Ability: 6<br>
Warrior<br>
Lore: Dark Jedi, Spy, Senator<br>
Game Text: Once per turn, search your reserve deck for a Lightsaber of any kind. It may deploy on you for free and reguardless of all requirements. During a battle, may lose the lightsaber to use it {otherwise you may not use it}. Adds a battle destiny if in battle against Anakin Skywalker. Immune to attrition &lt;6.<br>
<br>
Jango Fett:<br>
Deploy: 5<br>
Forfeit: 5<br>
Power: 4<br>
Ability: 3<br>
Armor: 5<br>
Warrior<br>
Pilot<br>
Lore: Bounty Hunter<br>
Game Text: When in battle with a clone or Mandalorian, or any character with Fett in title, opponent&#146;s destinies are -1. Opponent may not fire more then 2 weapons per battle. Opponent&#146;s Jedi are Immune to Attrition -1 here {if Jedi completly Immune to Attrition, only Immune to &lt;7}. Immune to attrition &lt;4. Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots.<br>
<br>
Light Side:<br>
<br>
Anakin Skywalker<br>
Deploy: 6<br>
Forfeit: 9<br>
Power: 6<br>
Ability: 5<br>
Lore: Jedi, General<br>
Warrior<br>
Pilot<br>
Game Text: Adds 4 to power of anything he pilots. May not be placed out of play. May not be deployed to table if Vader on table. While on table, if Padme also on table, and Luke or Leia not on table, opponent may lose 5 force to place Anakin in Lost Pile, and place Vader in play {this may only be done during opponent&#146;s deploy phase, and opponent must pay the correct amount of Force to deploy Vader}. Your battle destinies are +3. Immune to Attrition &lt;6.<br>
<br>
Obi-Wan Kenobi, Mentor<br>
Deploy: 6<br>
Forfeit: 8<br>
Power: 6<br>
Ability: 6<br>
Warrior<br>
Lore: Jedi, General<br>
Game Text: If at same site as Anakin, for opponent to &quot;cross him&quot; its doubled. Once per turn during your control phase, may search for Gift of the Mentor from your reserve deck. If no Clones present, your power is +1, if Clones present, power +2. Anakin is Forfeit +3 at same site. Immune to Attrition &lt;6.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
END SPOILERS<br>
<br>
Other ideas for Prize Support, being if able to, of course Packs. Or, if you are able to get any other form of thing, you can easily use that.<br>
<br>
<br>
What else can we do &#146;all great and smart one&#146;? <br>
<br>
Well, you can always do a league. A league is a great way to keep the game alive. Its easy, and can be extremely fun. Set up some good fundamental rules {no challanging people 3 times in a row, etc. etc. etc.} so that everything is fair, and it shall go all according to plan.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Well, I hope these ideas help you keep this game alive.<br>
<br>
Thanxs for reading.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
